Unstuffed Cabbage Casseroles
  --Lauren Miyashiro

Cooking spray
1 large head cabbage, roughly chopped
2 tbsp evoo
1 large onion, chopped
3 cloves garlic, minced
1 lb ground beef
2 tbsp tomato paste
14.5 oz can chopped tomatoes
1 c rice
3 c low-sodium chicken broth (or water)
chopped parsley, for serving

Preheat oven to 350F and grease a 9x13" baking dish with cooking spray. In a large dutch oven or pot over medium heat, heat oil. Add onion and cook until soft,`5 min. Stir in garlic and cook until fragrant, 1 min more. Add ground beef, breaking up meat with a wooden spoon, and cook until no longer pink, ~6 min. Drain fat. Return skillet to heat. Stir in tomato paste until beef is coated, then add chopped tomatoes, rice, and 2 c broth. Season with oregano, salt, and pepper. Bring mixture to a simmer and cook 10 min, stirring frequently to prevent rice from scorching. Gradually stir in cabbage and cook until slightly wilted, 5 min. Stir in remaining 1 c broth. Transfer mixture to prepared baking dish and cover dish with foil. Bake until rice is tender, ~40 min. Garnish with parsley before serving.

